-- Bayer Acquires New Zealand's Largest Privately Held Animal Health Company
-- B y   A n g e l a   C u l l e n
-- 2010-11-03T07:04:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/bayer-acquires-new-zealand-s-largest-privately-held-animal-health-company.html
Bayer AG  purchased Bomac Group, New
Zealand’s largest privately held animal health company, adding
290 products and 200 staff. Leverkusen, Germany-based Bayer
didn’t disclose financial details in an e-mailed statement
today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  